	<h2 class="c11">
		<a name="h.8790yzey55pn"></a><span>1. Overview</span>
	</h2>
	<p class="c11">
		<span class="c0">This document aims to show the architecture,
			design and technology behind the website. Such as 3-tier architecture
			implemented by MVC design pattern combining with DAO, and Java EE
			technology which includes java servlet, JSP, JDBC and Java EE
			Security Role.</span>
	</p>
	<h2 class="c11">
		<a name="h.5boc1cgov89k"></a><span>2. 3-Tier Architecture and
			MVC</span>
	</h2>
	<h3 class="c11">
		<a name="h.etr6fqbp0klz"></a><span>2.1 Browsing Product
			Process:</span>
	</h3>
	<p class="c11">
		<span class="c0">User clicks on any category on the product
			menu to send a request action </span><span class="c0 c4">product</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;and parameter </span><span class="c0 c4">category</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;to servlet </span><span class="c0 c4">MainController.
		</span><span class="c0">In the MainController, the parameter uses as
			an ID to initialise the correct list </span><span class="c0 c4">Product
			Model </span><span class="c0">by connecting to the Database via JDBC.
			After instantiating successfully </span><span class="c0 c4">Product
			Model</span><span class="c0">, the </span><span class="c0 c4">MainController
		</span><span class="c0">dispatches those of objects back to the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">View</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;JSP file which
			is </span><span class="c0 c4">products.jsp</span><span class="c0">.
			In order to display product&rsquo;s information the product.jsp </span><span
			class="c0 c4">View </span><span class="c0">will invoke back to
			the Product </span><span class="c0 c4">Model</span><span class="c0">.
			Finally, the </span><span class="c0 c4">product.jsp</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span
			class="c0 c4">View </span><span class="c0">response the
			information to the client browser and display them.</span>
	</p>
	<p class="c11 c13">
		<span class="c0"></span>
	</p>
	<p class="c11 c13">
		<span class="c0"></span>
	</p>
	<br/><br/>
	<p class="c11">
		<img height="183" src="images/image02.png" width="602">
	</p>
	<h3 class="c11 c14">
		<a name="h.v2qq52d25i8z"></a>
	</h3>
	<h3 class="c11">
		<a name="h.4205f0s5m72b"></a><span>2.2 Product Ordering Process</span>
	</h3>
	<p class="c11">
		<span class="c0">User from the products page clicks on add cart
			button on each product to send request action </span><span class="c0 c4">add
			cart</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;and parameter </span><span class="c0 c4">productId</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;to servlet </span><span class="c0 c4">CartController.
		</span><span class="c0">In the </span><span class="c0 c4">CartController</span><span
			class="c0">, the parameter </span><span class="c0 c4">productId</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;uses as an ID to find the product information
			by connecting to the Database via JDBC then instantiate the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">Product and Cart Model</span><span class="c0">.
			In this case, after instantiating successfully </span><span class="c0 c4">Model</span><span
			class="c0">, the </span><span class="c0 c4">CartController </span><span
			class="c0">saves the cart&rsquo;s information into a session
			and then</span><span class="c0 c4">&nbsp;</span><span class="c0">send
			another request </span><span class="c0 c4">action cart </span><span
			class="c0">and </span><span class="c0 c4">the session cart</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;to the </span><span class="c0 c4">MainController</span><span
			class="c0">. From there, the </span><span class="c0 c4">MainController
		</span><span class="c0">dispatches the object &nbsp;back to the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">View</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;JSP file which
			is </span><span class="c0 c4">cart.jsp</span><span class="c0">. In
			order to display cart information, the </span><span class="c0 c4">cart.jsp</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c0 c4">View </span><span
			class="c0">will invoke back to the </span><span class="c0 c4">Product
			and Cart</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span class="c0 c4">Model
		</span><span class="c0">to retrieve the product info. Finally, the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">cart.jsp</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span
			class="c0 c4">View </span><span class="c0">responses the
			information to the client browser and display them. </span>
	</p>
	<p class="c11 c13">
		<span class="c0"></span>
	</p>
	<br/><br/>
	<p class="c11">
		<img height="298" src="images/image00.png" width="602">
	</p>
