	</p>
	<h3 class="c11">
		<a name="h.tn2izh619dx8"></a><span>2.3 Purchase Process</span>
	</h3>
	<p class="c11">
		<span class="c0">From the checkout page where user enter the
			information. After filling all the form which is triggered some
			validations the user information will be stored into a session. After
			that, the user clicks on proceed button to send request action </span><span
			class="c0 c4">proceed</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;and to
			servlet </span><span class="c0 c4">OrderController. </span><span class="c0">In
			the </span><span class="c0 c4">OrderController</span><span class="c0">,
			the user session will be saved into the Database via JDBC then that
			session will be removed. At the same time, the cart session which is
			stored from the ordering product process will also be saved into
			Database. After saving successfully the user and cart info, the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">OrderController</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;will
			process the </span><span class="c0 c4">Order Model</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;then
			save it into Database. After that, the </span><span class="c0 c4">OrderController</span><span
			class="c0">&nbsp;send back the </span><span class="c0 c4">orderId
		</span><span class="c0">to the </span><span class="c0 c4">MainController
		</span><span class="c0">in order to dispatch it to the </span><span
			class="c0 c4">success.jsp View.</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;
			Finally, the </span><span class="c0 c4">success.jsp</span><span class="c0">&nbsp;</span><span
			class="c0 c4">View </span><span class="c0">responses the
			information to the client browser and display them. </span>
	</p>
