	<h2 class="c11">
		<a name="h.y8nfsfnzeljy"></a><span>4. Assumptions</span>
	</h2>
	<ol class="c6" start="1">
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">There is no viewing product detail because all information of the product which are showed in the browsing pages.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">Each time customers
				purchase, their information will be saved it into database.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">There is only new
				customer. One purchase one new customer.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">Each purchase contains
				only one customer and one cart.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">Searching order returns
				only one order for each customer.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">In the cart process, when
				customer update the quantity product which is equal or less than 0
				that product will be removed. If customer enters alpha character the
				original quantity will be kept.</span></li>
		<li class="c2"><span class="c0">In the admin page update
				status order, there are only 3 code </span><span class="c0 c4">ORDERED</span><span
			class="c0">, </span><span class="c0 c4">SENT</span><span class="c0">,
		</span><span class="c0 c4">PAID. </span><span class="c0">So If there
				is invalid input, the status simply rollbacks the original status.</span></li>
	</ol>
